,'2025-05-31 11:16:10.694000','2025-07-07 06:25:11.032000',NULL,8,36,'en','HAECO Aircraft Maintenance Hangar No. 2 Main Contract Works','Hong Kong Aircraft Engineering Co., Ltd.','10 November 2005 - 20 December 2006','<p>The construction of the Hangar No. 2 will provide the Client with a new facility in excess of 14,000m2 in area which will be able to accommodate two + one wide-bodied aircraft at one time and will have the capability to undertake all maintenance and modification work currently handled at HKIA including but not limited to: heavy maintenance, modification, repair and overhaul of commercial aircraft and their components.</p><br/><p>The new steel hangar including foundation measured 170mx85m (14,450m2) on plan and is located to the east of the existing Aircraft Maintenance Hangar No. 1 facing the South Runway. The minimum clear span and headroom of the hangar required are 157m (wide) and 27m (high) respectively.</p>',14.00),(88,'giw4gxil7ienmlnc8ohrtv0s','Airfield Stop Bar Relocation Works (Contract No. P318)','2025-05-31 11:17:41.809000','2025-07-07 06:25:13.506000',NULL,8,36,'en','Airfield Stop Bar Relocation Works','Airport Authority Hong Kong','19 July 2005 - 09 April 2006','<p>The entire installation works is carried out at night to minimize disturbance to the airfields. Daily detail works plans are carefully planed and perfectly orchestrated at night to maximize productivity under the tight working hours. Although the physical airfield works are only carried out at night, the project requires a 24-hours-a-day input from the project team.</p><br/><p>Pre-cast concrete bases (constructed on site during the day) are perfect for a quick installation of the stop bar light system.</p><br/><p>The transformer housings units of the airfield ground lighting system are imported directly from the United States to meet the stringent requirements for airfields usages.</p>',15.00),(90,'eav46nnozklbih5udqfxup96','香港国际机场跑道灯号迁移工程 (合约编号：P318)','2025-05-31 11:18:38.028000','2025-07-07 06:25:20.256000',NULL,8,36,'zh-CN','香港国际机场跑道灯号迁移工程','香港机场管理局','2005 年 07 月 19 日 - 2006 年 04 月 09 日','<p>整个安装工程需在夜间进行以减少对机场运作的影响。由于工程时间紧凑，故需精心策划详细的施工进度计划，使晚上的生产力发挥至最大。虽然劳动工作只能在夜间进行，但工程筹划小组仍需要24小时投入到项目团队里。</p><br/><p>预制混凝土地基（在白天预制）是非常适合用作快速安装杆照明系统上。</p><br/><p>机场地面照明系统的变压器装置需由美国直接进口，以满足严格的机场用途要求。</p>',15.00),(92,'oz2absqimfdhowzneqcf5mvb','香港國際機場跑道燈號遷移工程 (合約編號：P318)','2025-05-31 11:19:28.134000','2025-07-07 06:25:20.837000',NULL,8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','香港國際機場跑道燈號遷移工程','香港機場管理局','2005 年 07 月 19 日 - 2006 年 04 月 09 日','<p>整個安裝工程需在夜間進行以減少對機場運作的影響。由於工程時間緊湊，故需精心策劃詳細的施工進度，使晚上的生產力發揮至最大。雖然勞動工作只能在夜間進行，但工程籌劃小組仍需要24小時投入的項目團隊。</p><br/><p>預製混凝土地基（在白天預製）是非常適合用作快速安裝桿照明系統上。</p><br/><p>機場地面照明系統的變壓器裝置需由美國直接進口，以滿足嚴格的機場用途要求。</p>',15.00),(94,'n0riimawpx7t2kexnto1kj3w','香港國際機場航天城停車場工程 (合約編號：P336)','2025-05-31 13:08:33.337000','2025-07-07 06:25:20.753000',NULL,8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','香港國際機場航天城停車場工程','香港機場管理局','2005 年 05 月 31 日 - 2005 年 12 月 20 日','<p>我們公司是香港第一間應用GFA鋪面物的公司。GFA是混合顆粒材枓和&#x27;粉煤灰&#x27;或煤灰。GFA是一種需緩慢硬化的混合體，在短期內是一個未綁定的材料，需較長的處理時間，但中至長期的結構表現與慣用的材料一樣，如瀝青。</p><br/><p>GFA是煤發電的副產廢物，是一種合乎經濟和環保供選擇的鋪面物。</p>',16.00),(96,'kxkitkjaxyu98mkh3zfuq1kg','香港国际机场航天城停车场工程 (合约编号：P336)','2025-05-31 13:09:34.172000','2025-07-07 06:25:18.861000',NULL,8,36,'zh-CN','香港国际机场航天城停车场工程','香港机场管理局','2005 年 05 月 31 日 - 2005 年 12 月 20 日','<p>我们公司是香港第一间应用GFA铺面物的公司。GFA是混合颗粒材枓和&#x27;粉煤灰&#x27;或煤灰。GFA是一种需缓慢硬化的混合体，在短期内是一个未绑定的材料，需较长的处理时间，但中至长期的结构表现与惯用的材料一样，如沥青。</p><br/><p>GFA是煤发电的副产废物，是一种合乎经济和环保供选择的铺面物。</p>',16.00),(98,'v31e96y7ds5j0epo6rbri5ma','Sky City Car Park and Utility Works (Contract No. P336)','2025-05-31 13:10:32.490000','2025-07-07 06:25:12.639000',NULL,8,36,'en','Sky City Car Park and Utility Works','Airport Authority Hong Kong','31 May 2005 - 20 December 2005','<p>Our company is the first to apply the GFA pavement in Hong Kong. GFA is the acronym for granular materials treated with ‘fly ash’ or PFA. GFA is a slow setting, slow hardening mixture which has the benefit of an unbound material in the short-term allowing longer handling time, and as a bound material in the medium to long term provides equivalent if not better structural characteristics of conventional bound materials such as bituminous base course.</p><br/><p>GFA utilizes PFA, a by-product waste from coal-fired energy generation, making it a more economical and environmentally friendly pavement alternative.</p>',16.00),(100,'gah5zn8m9ybn6fqm3zflmpoo','Maintenance Apron Expansion Works (Contract No. P316C)','2025-05-31 13:12:35.322000','2025-07-07 06:25:10.884000',NULL,8,36,'en','Maintenance Apron Expansion Works','Airport Authority Hong Kong','26 May 2005 - 28 March 2006','<p>Due to the highly sensitive nature of the area, access is a major obstacle. Construction vehicles and staff have to be escorted and go through security checks each time they enter and exit the site for security reasons.</p><br/><p>The supply of fresh concrete to the site next to the airfield runway poses another major constraint. Special on site concrete batching plants were constructed. The paving of the Pavement Quality Concrete requires a special automatic paver from Germany, the Wirtgen Slip form paver SP500 to achieve an extremely accurate finish of the concrete surface.</p><br/><p>Depending on the ambient conditions such as the atmospheric moisture content and temperature, appropriate curing methods plays an important role in achieving the required high quality surface finish.</p>',17.00),(102,'g458qlu64xy0um5n2vqh8lgx','香港国际机场维修停机坪扩建工程 (合约编号：P316C)','2025-05-31 13:13:54.377000','2025-07-07 06:25:20.356000',NULL,8,36,'zh-CN','香港国际机场维修停机坪扩建工程','香港机场管理局','2005 年 05 月 26 日 - 2006 年 03 月 28 日','<p>由于工程在高度敏感地区进行，进出地盘是一个重大的难题。基于保安理由，施工车辆每次需在工作人员陪同下，并要经过安全检查才可进出地盘。</p><br/><p>供应混凝土到机场跑道旁边的地盘是另一项挑战。我们运用了特别的的混凝土配料机。此项目对混凝土路面有特别的质量要求，需用来自德国的SP500自流物料，以达到一个非常准确的混凝土完成面。</p><br/><p>根据不同的环境条件，如大气中的水分含量和温度，适当的养护方法以达到高品质的表面有着重要的作用。</p>',17.00),(104,'ysyhp2bryvsvk1uncoxdevgs','香港國際機場維修停機坪擴建工程 (合約編號：P316C)','2025-05-31 13:14:58.861000','2025-07-07 06:25:20.347000',NULL,8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','香港國際機場維修停機坪擴建工程','香港機場管理局','2005 年 05 月 26 日 - 2006 年 03 月 28 日','<p>由於工程在高度敏感地區進行，進出地盤是一個重大的難題。基於保安理由，施工車輛每次需在工作人員陪同下，並要經過安全檢查才可進出地盤。</p><br/><p>供應混凝土到機場跑道旁邊的地盤是另一項挑戰。我們運用了特別的的混凝土配料機。此項目對混凝土路面有特別的質量要求，需用來自德國的SP500自流物料，以達到一個非常準確的混凝土完成面。</p><br/><p>根據不同的環境條件，如大氣中的水分含量和溫度，適當的養護方法以達到高品質的表面有著重要的作用。</p>',17.00),(107,'f27qmuf77dqyl8q0hrinb1cr',' 香港國際機場西碼頭改善工程 (合約編號：P313)','2025-05-31 13:34:02.799000','2025-07-07 06:25:19.424000',NULL,8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','香港國際機場西碼頭改善工程','香港機場管理局','2005 年 05 月 17 日 - 2006 年 02 月 10 日','<p>該項目的所有工作人員均具有豐富經驗和熟悉香港機場工地規章和程序。這是我們提高工作進度的重大的優勢。</p><br/><p>P313消防系統-水簾系統</p><br/><p>水簾系統為西船隻停泊處提供保護。該系統包括消防水泵，集水花灑閥系統，水簾進水口，噴嘴，壓力開關，管道和閥門 ...等。一個儲存65000升的玻璃纖維水箱服務整個水簾系統。水箱直接從現有U/G消防供水管道裝滿,。兩個加壓泵提供所需的流量和壓力而另一個操控水泵維持系統的壓力。</p><br/><p>固定泡沫系統</p><br/><p>固定泡沫系統提供保護燃料歧管，進站燃料接待多方面的。該系統包括消防泵，玻璃纖維水箱，泡沫水箱，集水花灑閥系統，遙遠控制器 /噴嘴，泡沫調和器，濃縮泡沫，消防進水口，遙遠控制器，電池，電池充電器，水管和閥門等... 一個儲存90000升的玻璃纖維水箱服務整個泡沫系統。兩個加壓泵提供所需的流量和壓力而另一個操控水泵維持系統的壓力。</p>',18.00),(109,'iyav06tfzcz4pal3z1tqk44r','香港国际机场西码头改善工程 (合约编号：P313)','2025-05-31 13:35:29.996000','2025-07-07 06:25:21.109000',NULL,8,36,'zh-CN','香港国际机场西码头改善工程','香港机场管理局','2005 年 05 月 17 日 - 2006 年 02 月 10 日','<p>该项目的所有工作人员均具有丰富经验和熟悉香港机场工地规章和程序。这是我们提高工作进度的重大的优势。</p><br/><p>P313消防系统-水帘系统</p><br/><p>水帘系统为西船只停泊处提供保护。该系统包括消防水泵，集水花洒阀系统，水帘进水口，喷嘴，压力开关，管道和阀门 ...等。一个储存65000升的玻璃纤维水箱服务整个水帘系统。水箱直接从现有U/G消防供水管道装满,。两个加压泵提供所需的流量和压力而另一个操控水泵维持系统的压力。</p><br/><p>固定泡沫系统</p><br/><p>固定泡沫系统提供保护燃料歧管，进站燃料接待多方面的。该系统包括消防泵，玻璃纤维水箱，泡沫水箱，集水花洒阀系统，遥远控制器 /喷嘴，泡沫调和器，浓缩泡沫，消防进水口，遥远控制器，电池，电池充电器，水管和阀门等... 一个储存90000升的玻璃纤维水箱服务整个泡沫系统。两个加压泵提供所需的流量和压力而另一个操控水泵维持系统的压力。</p>',18.00),(111,'zb2jrgdikx9jz6wo5szouc4l','West Quay AFS Upgrading Works (Contract No. P313)','2025-05-31 13:36:36.141000','2025-07-07 06:25:13.313000',NULL,8,36,'en','West Quay AFS Upgrading Works','Airport Authority Hong Kong','17 May 2005 - 10 February 2006','<p>All staff on the project has extensive experiences and familiarity with the Hong Kong Airport work site regulations and procedures. This is a major advantage in getting up to speed with the works.</p><br/><p>P313 Fire Services System-Drencher System</p><br/><p>The drencher system provides protection to the west quay. The system comprises of fire pumps, deluge valve set, drencher inlets, nozzles, pressure switches, pipe works and valves…etc. One 65,000-litres fiberglass drencher water storage tank serves the entire drencher system. The water storage tank refills directly from the existing U/G F.S. town main water supply pipe. Two drencher booster pumps provide the required flow and pressure while one jockey pump maintains the system pressure.</p><br/><p>Fixed Foam System</p><br/><p>The fixed foam system provides protection to the pit for the fuel reception manifold. The system comprises fire pumps, fiberglass water tank, foam bladder tank, deluge valve sets, remote control monitors/nozzles, foam proportioners, foam concentrate, FS inlet, remote control units, batteries, battery charger, pipe works and valves…etc. One 90,000-litres fiberglass drencher water storage tank serves the entire fixed foam system. Two foam booster pumps provide the required flow and pressure while one jockey pump maintains the system pressure.</p>',18.00),(113,'zxfy2yty09b9o1och91k1dh9','Hong Kong International Airport – Cargo Apron Extension Works (Contract No. P306)','2025-05-31 13:38:08.887000','2025-07-07 06:25:12.554000',NULL,8,36,'en','Hong Kong International Airport – Cargo Apron Extension Works','Airport Authority Hong Kong','24 March 2004 - 31 May 2005','<p>Due to the highly sensitive nature of the area, access is a major obstacle. Construction vehicles have to be inspected and escorted every time they enter into the site for security reasons.</p><br/><p>The supply of fresh concrete into the site next to the airfield runway poses another major constraint. Special site concrete batching plants were constructed. The paving of the Pavement Quality Concrete requires a special automatic paver from Germany, the Wirtgen Slip form paver SP500 to achieve an extremely accurate quality finish of the concrete surface</p>',19.00),(115,'wm0kjao2yie5vfwwg7tngzm1','香港国际机场货运停机坪扩建工程 (合约编号：P306)','2025-05-31 13:39:16.736000','2025-07-07 06:25:21.074000',NULL,8,36,'zh-CN','香港国际机场货运停机坪扩建工程','香港机场管理局','2004 年 03 月 24 日 - 2005 年 05 月 31 日','<p>工程地点在高度敏感范围，令进出地盘成为一个重大障碍。基于保安理由，每辆进出地盘的车辆都需要接受检查及护送进出地盘。</p><br/><p>在机场跑道旁边运送混凝土令施工上有很大的限制。因此特制了混凝土配料设备。此工程对铺设路面的混凝土有严格的质量要求，需从德国进口，以达到非常精确的混凝土路面。</p>',19.00),(117,'k9m3dj8znh97oi8baukxirm9','香港國際機場貨運停機坪擴建工程 (合約編號：P306)','2025-05-31 13:40:28.624000','2025-07-07 06:25:21.182000',NULL,8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','香港國際機場貨運停機坪擴建工程','香港機場管理局','2004 年 03 月 24 日 - 2005 年 05 月 31 日','<p>工程地點在高度敏感範圍，令進出地盤成為一個重大障礙。基於保安理由，每輛進出地盤的車輛都需要接受檢查及護送進出地盤。</p><br/><p>在機場跑道旁邊運送混凝土令施工上有很大的限制。因此特製了混凝土配料設備。此工程對鋪設路面的混凝土有嚴格的質量要求，需從德國進口，以達到高度品質的混凝土路面。</p>',19.00),(119,'ojhriymqjdzwvle3n5n2fvqe','西北客運大樓及停機坪 (香港機場管理局 合約編號304)','2025-05-31 13:41:32.449000','2025-07-07 06:25:21.077000',NULL,8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','西北客運大樓及停機坪','香港機場管理局','1997 年 09 月 01 日 - 1999 年 12 月 31 日','<p>本專案包括建造香港國際機場之西北客運大樓，十一條連接橋及占地十萬平方呎之停機坪。爲順利完成本專案，承建商面對不同的挑戰。由於施工期間，需要確保機場的日常運作不受影響，承建商採取了嚴格的控制措施，包括管制工人及機械的活動範圍等，有效地控制及減低施工期間對機場的影響。除此之外，鋼結構組成的客運大樓屋頂也是一個很大的挑戰。由於本工程的西北客運大樓是以45度角與主客運大樓交接。因此，鋼結構屋頂形成了非常複雜的幾何設計，我們採用了先進的測量技術及相關的儀器，成功地完成了組裝的任務，確保工程的質量。在鋼結構的接駁方法上，我們選擇了縲絲接合的設計以取代焊接法。因此方法更能配合安裝現場的施工環境，減短安裝時間。另一方面，也消除了機管局對焊接法所産生的火花而導致影響機場運作的疑慮。</p>',20.00),(121,'pdrzzfn3ym95v35bpnwovmx9','西北客运大楼及停机坪 (香港机场管理局 合约编号304)','2025-05-31 13:43:04.666000','2025-07-07 06:25:18.935000',NULL,8,36,'zh-CN','西北客运大楼及停机坪','香港机场管理局','1997 年 09 月 01 日 - 1999 年 12 月 31 日','<p>本项目包括建造香港国际机场西北客运大楼，十一条连接桥及占地十万平方尺的停机坪。为顺利完成本项目，承建商面对许多挑战。由于施工期间，需要确保机场的日常运作不受影响，承建商采取了严格的控制措施，包括管制工人及机械的活动范围等，有效地控制及减低施工期间对机场的影响。除此之外，钢结构构成的客运大楼屋顶也是一个很大的挑战。由于本工程的西北客运大楼是以45度角与主客运大楼交接。因此，钢结构屋顶形成了非常复杂的几何设计，我们采用了先进的测量技术及相关的仪器，成功地完成了组装的任务，确保工程的质量。在钢结构的接驳方法上，我们选择了缧丝接合法以取代焊接法。因为此方法更能符合安装现场的施工环境要求，缩短安装时间。另一方面，也消除了机管局对焊接法产生的火花会影响机场运作的疑虑。</p>',20.00),(123,'v6ro94bu5h5btt6y3r7tgrxy','Northwest Concourse and Apron Works (AA Contract 304)','2025-05-31 13:44:49.243000','2025-07-07 06:25:10.883000',NULL,8,36,'en','Northwest Concourse and Apron Works','Airport Authority Hong Kong','01 September 1997 - 31 December 1999','<p>The contract to build the concourse extension, eleven fixed link bridges and 100,000ft². of apron area was awarded to the joint venture between Zen Pacific and Shui On. The project presented a number of challenges, not least the construction of the steel roof. The roof has a particularly complex geometry as the Northwest Concourse branches out from the main building at a 45-degree angle, which gives rise to grids of parallelograms with no right angles. A bolted design was chosen for the roof instead of the welded method used on the main terminal. The method of construction was chosen because it was more economical given the small number of roof modules involved and it improved installation time significantly. In addition, the method addressed the Airport Authority’s concerns over sparks from welding, which might have interfered with the airport’s operation.</p>',20.00),(150,'r50pn5hhx4cfr2qh3xf6lrtb','Hong Kong Business Aviation Centre Main Contract for the construction of the Hong Kong Business Aviation Centre Hangar 2','2025-05-31 11:01:18.395000','2025-07-07 06:25:10.622000','2025-07-07 06:25:10.960000',8,36,'en','Hong Kong Business Aviation Centre Main Contract for the construction of the Hong Kong Business Aviation Centre Hangar 2','Hong Kong Business Aviation Centre, Ltd.','14 November 2006 - 15 August 2007','<p>Major works consist of:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of an air-craft hanger building including foundations, structural steel roof and superstructure, wall and roof claddings, supply and install M&amp;E equipment and Building Services.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of a single storey ancillary office building with RC structure including the associated architectural finishes, M&amp; E and Building Services.</li></ul>',11.00),(151,'ezpe1771sjuljkddvevf341o','Hong Kong International Airport Contract P581 – East Hall Expansion Works','2025-05-31 07:12:16.946000','2025-07-07 06:25:10.592000','2025-07-07 06:25:10.969000',8,36,'en','Hong Kong International Airport Contract P581 – East Hall Expansion Works','Hong Kong Airport Authority','30 June 2017 - 30 April 2022','<p>HKAA is planning to enhance the passenger and baggage processing facilities in Terminal 1 (T1) through expansion and modi­fication works to meet the growing demand at Hong Kong International Airport.</p><p>The works will comprise the building extensions at North and South junctions between the airside East Hall and Central Concourse, which also comprise the modifi­cation works providing accommodation for additional passenger facilities and circulation space and link bridges to improve connectivity in the existing East Hall.</p>',3.00),(152,'zjpazmp35tnykoipkgqyo7at','Refurbishment of Nursery Rooms at PTB (Contract M988)','2025-05-31 10:59:20.221000','2025-07-07 06:25:10.623000','2025-07-07 06:25:10.980000',8,36,'en','Refurbishment of Nursery Rooms at PTB','Airport Authority Hong Kong','15 November 2006 - 30 April 2007','<p>The works consist of the Refurbishment of 16 nos. Nursery Rooms at levels 4, 5, 6 and 7 of the Passenger Terminal Buildings</p>',10.00),(153,'n2kmnq9xhiykwy4e9otg6c41','Refurbishment of Smoking Lounges at PTB (Contract M980)','2025-05-31 11:10:44.512000','2025-07-07 06:25:10.651000','2025-07-07 06:25:11.084000',8,36,'en','Refurbishment of Smoking Lounges at PTB','Airport Authority Hong Kong','17 March 2006 - 19 September 2006','<p>Refurbishment works to 10 nos. of smoking lounges located at levels 5 and 6 of the Passenger Terminal Building (PTB)</p>',13.00),(154,'gah5zn8m9ybn6fqm3zflmpoo','Maintenance Apron Expansion Works (Contract No. P316C)','2025-05-31 13:12:35.322000','2025-07-07 06:25:10.884000','2025-07-07 06:25:11.107000',8,36,'en','Maintenance Apron Expansion Works','Airport Authority Hong Kong','26 May 2005 - 28 March 2006','<p>Due to the highly sensitive nature of the area, access is a major obstacle. Construction vehicles and staff have to be escorted and go through security checks each time they enter and exit the site for security reasons.</p><br/><p>The supply of fresh concrete to the site next to the airfield runway poses another major constraint. Special on site concrete batching plants were constructed. The paving of the Pavement Quality Concrete requires a special automatic paver from Germany, the Wirtgen Slip form paver SP500 to achieve an extremely accurate finish of the concrete surface.</p><br/><p>Depending on the ambient conditions such as the atmospheric moisture content and temperature, appropriate curing methods plays an important role in achieving the required high quality surface finish.</p>',17.00),(155,'l82m93dnvvuuff12dv84mkkh',' Hong Kong International Airport Contract C18W02 - lntermodal Transfer Terminal (ITT) Building','2025-05-31 07:10:50.694000','2025-07-07 06:25:10.815000','2025-07-07 06:25:11.405000',8,36,'en','Hong Kong International Airport Contract C18W02 - lntermodal Transfer Terminal (ITT) Building','Hong Kong Airport Authority','31 December 2018 - 31 August 2024','<p>This project is an extension of the existing SkyPier at the Hong Kong International Airport (HKIA), extending it from Level 1 to the roof (corresponding to Level 5 of the ITT Building). The purpose of this extension is to serve transfer passengers arriving and leaving HKIA via bonded bus from/to the Pearl River Delta, in addition to the current cross-boundary ferry service.</p><p>The works comprise the construction of the new Intermodal Transfer Terminal Building, modifications to the existing SkyPier, associated modifications at Terminal 1 East Hall, utilities and external road works.</p>',2.00),(156,'xvrcmr8c1vzgh74gthf608gi','HAECO Aircraft Maintenance Hangar No. 2 Main Contract Works','2025-05-31 11:16:10.694000','2025-07-07 06:25:11.032000','2025-07-07 06:25:12.409000',8,36,'en','HAECO Aircraft Maintenance Hangar No. 2 Main Contract Works','Hong Kong Aircraft Engineering Co., Ltd.','10 November 2005 - 20 December 2006','<p>The construction of the Hangar No. 2 will provide the Client with a new facility in excess of 14,000m2 in area which will be able to accommodate two + one wide-bodied aircraft at one time and will have the capability to undertake all maintenance and modification work currently handled at HKIA including but not limited to: heavy maintenance, modification, repair and overhaul of commercial aircraft and their components.</p><br/><p>The new steel hangar including foundation measured 170mx85m (14,450m2) on plan and is located to the east of the existing Aircraft Maintenance Hangar No. 1 facing the South Runway. The minimum clear span and headroom of the hangar required are 157m (wide) and 27m (high) respectively.</p>',14.00),(157,'v6ro94bu5h5btt6y3r7tgrxy','Northwest Concourse and Apron Works (AA Contract 304)','2025-05-31 13:44:49.243000','2025-07-07 06:25:10.883000','2025-07-07 06:25:12.398000',8,36,'en','Northwest Concourse and Apron Works','Airport Authority Hong Kong','01 September 1997 - 31 December 1999','<p>The contract to build the concourse extension, eleven fixed link bridges and 100,000ft². of apron area was awarded to the joint venture between Zen Pacific and Shui On. The project presented a number of challenges, not least the construction of the steel roof. The roof has a particularly complex geometry as the Northwest Concourse branches out from the main building at a 45-degree angle, which gives rise to grids of parallelograms with no right angles. A bolted design was chosen for the roof instead of the welded method used on the main terminal. The method of construction was chosen because it was more economical given the small number of roof modules involved and it improved installation time significantly. In addition, the method addressed the Airport Authority’s concerns over sparks from welding, which might have interfered with the airport’s operation.</p>',20.00),(158,'y53fmoneiazq41oohfc25fdi','Midfield Parking Stands Upgrading Works (Contract No. P343)','2025-05-31 08:48:49.756000','2025-07-07 06:25:11.162000','2025-07-07 06:25:12.583000',8,36,'en','Midfield Parking Stands Upgrading Works','Airport Authority Hong Kong','23 November 2006 - 05 August 2007','<p>The works consist of the Manufacture, Supply, Construction, Installation, Testing Commissioning and Design of the Midfield Parking Stands Upgrading Works</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Site Clearance</li></ul><p>     o	Taking down of street lights and delivery for storage;</p><p>     o	Removal of taxiway edge lights and delivery for storage</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Airfield Pavement Works</li></ul><p>     o	Earthworks, asphalt pavements, stormwater drainage, AGL base can, communication and telephone cabling and associated drawpits and ductings and apron markings</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>High Mast Lighting</li></ul><p>     o	Foundation, mast and associated cables and light fittings</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>System works</li></ul><p>      o	Emergency telephone system, lightning warning system, earthing protection, Movement Area Guidance Signs and SCADA system</p><br/><br/>',8.00),(159,'mhwqlqyj9whur19quxfp8hml','Hong Kong International Airport Contract C18W10 - North Commercial District Footbridge 1','2025-05-31 07:05:36.276000','2025-07-07 06:25:21.541000','2025-07-07 06:25:12.610000',8,36,'en','Hong Kong International Airport Contract C18W10 - North Commercial District Footbridge 1','Hong Kong Airport Authority','03 June 2019 - 30 June 2022','<p>The Government supports HKAA to develop the Airport North Commercial District (NCD) as a new retail, dining and entertainment hub, viewing it as an important economic initiative for the &quot;bridgehead economy&quot; of the Hong Kong-Zhuhai-Macao Bridge, generating investment, business and jobs while enhancing HKIA&#x27;s global competitiveness by aligning with the &quot;skycity&quot; concept seen at major airports.</p><p>This project comprises the construction of one of the pedestrian footbridges, namely Footbridge 1, connecting the West Lobby of AWE in the north and Site A1a and Site A1b of the SKYCITY in the south.</p>',1.00),(160,'zxfy2yty09b9o1och91k1dh9','Hong Kong International Airport – Cargo Apron Extension Works (Contract No. P306)','2025-05-31 13:38:08.887000','2025-07-07 06:25:12.554000','2025-07-07 06:25:12.988000',8,36,'en','Hong Kong International Airport – Cargo Apron Extension Works','Airport Authority Hong Kong','24 March 2004 - 31 May 2005','<p>Due to the highly sensitive nature of the area, access is a major obstacle. Construction vehicles have to be inspected and escorted every time they enter into the site for security reasons.</p><br/><p>The supply of fresh concrete into the site next to the airfield runway poses another major constraint. Special site concrete batching plants were constructed. The paving of the Pavement Quality Concrete requires a special automatic paver from Germany, the Wirtgen Slip form paver SP500 to achieve an extremely accurate quality finish of the concrete surface</p>',19.00),(161,'s1jvsowrtwdovzsakex7pawr',' Proposed Extension to Hangar Two (also known as “Hangar Three”)','2025-05-31 07:23:30.593000','2025-07-07 06:25:12.665000','2025-07-07 06:25:13.042000',8,36,'en','Proposed Extension to Hangar Two (also known as “Hangar Three”)','Hong Kong Business Aviation Centre, Ltd.','14 May 2011 - 31 May 2012','<p>The project is the extension of the existing Hangar Two operated by Hong Kong Business Aviation Centre, Ltd, namely as Hangar Three. The new third hangar aimed to complement the existing hangars in providing sufficient hangar spaces to meet the growing demand for aircraft hangars in Hong Kong.</p><p>Major works under the contract include the construction of an air-craft hangar building (approx. 80 m x 50m) with steel structure and metal cladding complete with hangar door, installation of the steel structure of the hangar building and providing all necessary protective painting at the fabrication yard and the construction of a group of one storey ancillary workshops, apron works, external paved roads, site works, plumbing, drainage installations and mechanical, ventilation and air conditioning and electrical installations.</p>',6.00),(162,'v31e96y7ds5j0epo6rbri5ma','Sky City Car Park and Utility Works (Contract No. P336)','2025-05-31 13:10:32.490000','2025-07-07 06:25:12.639000','2025-07-07 06:25:13.036000',8,36,'en','Sky City Car Park and Utility Works','Airport Authority Hong Kong','31 May 2005 - 20 December 2005','<p>Our company is the first to apply the GFA pavement in Hong Kong. GFA is the acronym for granular materials treated with ‘fly ash’ or PFA. GFA is a slow setting, slow hardening mixture which has the benefit of an unbound material in the short-term allowing longer handling time, and as a bound material in the medium to long term provides equivalent if not better structural characteristics of conventional bound materials such as bituminous base course.</p><br/><p>GFA utilizes PFA, a by-product waste from coal-fired energy generation, making it a more economical and environmentally friendly pavement alternative.</p>',16.00),(163,'ccqjqo0o2pb43r2debnpw5n9','New Midfield Screening Building (Contract P531)','2025-05-31 07:18:53.819000','2025-07-07 06:25:12.719000','2025-07-07 06:25:13.103000',8,36,'en','New Midfield Screening Building','Airport Authority Hong Kong','19 July 2011 - 03 September 2012','<p>In order to increase the capacity of Hong Kong International Airport to handle passenger and cargo transport, the Airport Authority has issued a Midfield development project to enhance Hong Kong&#x27;s competitiveness in the international transport industry and enable Hong Kong International Airport to continue serving as a regional and regional aviation hub for Asia and the world.</p><p>Our group was awarded one of the ancillary works under the Midfield Development Plan, a Design and Build project including design, supply, construction, testing and commissioning of the New Midfield Screening Building.</p>',5.00),(164,'sty9nruyn3d8tq09yksr8vsa','Construction and Fitting Out of Integrated Airport Centre (Contract M991)','2025-05-31 08:50:06.761000','2025-07-07 06:25:12.662000','2025-07-07 06:25:13.118000',8,36,'en','Construction and Fitting Out of Integrated Airport Centre','Airport Authority Hong Kong','16 November 2006 - 05 May 2007','<p>The works include the construction, fitting out and maintenance of the Integrated Airport Centre</p>',9.00),(165,'mavrzo7ley8uprxi007bcv6w','Business Aviation Centre Expansion Works (Contract No. P373)','2025-05-31 08:39:15.524000','2025-07-07 06:25:13.061000','2025-07-07 06:25:13.413000',8,36,'en','Business Aviation Centre Expansion Works','Airport Authority Hong Kong','16 November 2007 - 25 January 2009','<p>The works include an extension of existing Taxi lane Z3 and additional parking stands with BAC Expansion.</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Pavements works: earthworks; asphalt pavements; pavement quality concrete; tie-down anchors and line markings</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Utility works: oil separation system; storm water drainage; potable water main and fire hydrant system including pit hydrant; seawater supply system; pressured sewer system; communication ducting and cabling; and power ducting and cabling</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>System works; high mast lighting; earthing and lightning protection and warning system; all associated system including SCADA system and vehicle warning lights</li></ul>',7.00),(166,'zb2jrgdikx9jz6wo5szouc4l','West Quay AFS Upgrading Works (Contract No. P313)','2025-05-31 13:36:36.141000','2025-07-07 06:25:13.313000','2025-07-07 06:25:13.535000',8,36,'en','West Quay AFS Upgrading Works','Airport Authority Hong Kong','17 May 2005 - 10 February 2006','<p>All staff on the project has extensive experiences and familiarity with the Hong Kong Airport work site regulations and procedures. This is a major advantage in getting up to speed with the works.</p><br/><p>P313 Fire Services System-Drencher System</p><br/><p>The drencher system provides protection to the west quay. The system comprises of fire pumps, deluge valve set, drencher inlets, nozzles, pressure switches, pipe works and valves…etc. One 65,000-litres fiberglass drencher water storage tank serves the entire drencher system. The water storage tank refills directly from the existing U/G F.S. town main water supply pipe. Two drencher booster pumps provide the required flow and pressure while one jockey pump maintains the system pressure.</p><br/><p>Fixed Foam System</p><br/><p>The fixed foam system provides protection to the pit for the fuel reception manifold. The system comprises fire pumps, fiberglass water tank, foam bladder tank, deluge valve sets, remote control monitors/nozzles, foam proportioners, foam concentrate, FS inlet, remote control units, batteries, battery charger, pipe works and valves…etc. One 90,000-litres fiberglass drencher water storage tank serves the entire fixed foam system. Two foam booster pumps provide the required flow and pressure while one jockey pump maintains the system pressure.</p>',18.00),(167,'paaeepad6tis7idye35jznsk','Hong Kong International Airport Contract 3501- Antenna Farm and Sewage Pumping Station','2025-05-31 07:17:42.789000','2025-07-07 06:25:13.316000','2025-07-07 06:25:13.946000',8,36,'en','Hong Kong International Airport Contract 3501- Antenna Farm and Sewage Pumping Station','Hong Kong Airport Authority','12 June 2017 - 09 August 2018','<p>HKAA is required to relocate the existing antenna farm and one of the existing sewage pumping stations to facilitate the future expansion of Terminal 2.  This project includes the construction of the new antenna farm and sewage pumping station including associated utilities, road works and landscaping.</p><p>The works mainly comprise an antenna farm (including an antenna common equipment building and antenna tower) – complete with ABWF and building services; A sewage pumping station (Pumping</p><p>Station PS 12) – civil and structural engineering works only; Associated airport systems; Associated incoming and outgoing foul and grey water pipes; Associated roadworks, utilities, earth retaining walls and landscaping; Trenchless excavation for sewage rising mains; Associated testing and commissioning works; and All Temporary Works.</p>',4.00),(168,'ud5vjlltlrllhjp2010s2uny',' North Satellite Concourse Site Investigation Works (Contract No. P340)','2025-05-31 11:05:59.421000','2025-07-07 06:25:13.402000','2025-07-07 06:25:15.539000',8,36,'en','North Satellite Concourse Site Investigation Works','Airport Authority Hong Kong','28 June 2006 - 10 November 2006','<p>The works consist of ground investigation fieldwork and geotechnical instrumentation and monitoring</p>',12.00),(169,'giw4gxil7ienmlnc8ohrtv0s','Airfield Stop Bar Relocation Works (Contract No. P318)','2025-05-31 11:17:41.809000','2025-07-07 06:25:13.506000','2025-07-07 06:25:16.790000',8,36,'en','Airfield Stop Bar Relocation Works','Airport Authority Hong Kong','19 July 2005 - 09 April 2006','<p>The entire installation works is carried out at night to minimize disturbance to the airfields. Daily detail works plans are carefully planed and perfectly orchestrated at night to maximize productivity under the tight working hours. Although the physical airfield works are only carried out at night, the project requires a 24-hours-a-day input from the project team.</p><br/><p>Pre-cast concrete bases